{"text": "A lean-to addition is an appendix to an existing structure constructed to fulfill a new need. Sometimes, it covers an external staircase, as in a 15th-century addition against one of the walls of the large chapter room of Meaux Cathedral. Other uses include protecting entrances, or establishing covered markets outside existing buildings.", "embedding": [0.03550188, 0.044804793, -0.17638874, -0.066875465, 0.04277416, -0.013810667, 0.048269175, 0.012336075, 0.0010103725, -0.04858241, -0.035334405, 0.016587224, 0.081340834, 0.040211078, 0.03425634, -0.015367018, -0.00060692214, -0.017428344, 0.03624004, 0.020936176, -0.017864717, -0.032545432, -0.0067165885, 0.00618171, 0.041044727, 0.0060344064, 0.032858517, 0.0067752423, -0.028074007, 0.018188577, -0.0033696513, -0.05491133, 0.029930748, 0.011082638, -0.018304229, -0.051754013, 0.05101385, 0.05665424, -0.03959813, -0.04160334, -0.03292727, 0.0043472303, -0.021154586, -0.027513735, 0.038655467, -0.00050242624, 0.045952827, -0.020308806, 0.070938155, 0.023793167, -0.032169063, -0.037223104, -0.04384524, -0.015971633, 0.08232771, 0.009697126, 0.015913563, 0.0315017, 0.057979304, -0.020056011, 0.0687983, 0.03884473, 0.0045438968, 0.044633403, 0.031278815, -0.011743725, -0.0003836541, 0.045940403, -0.025966538, -0.030831082, 0.050497152, 0.0080968095, 0.05193563, 0.020813832, -0.026298286, -0.007152115, -0.019920219, -0.00903193, -0.007866674, 0.041496024, 0.016416952, -0.004849006, 0.08617037, 0.011612108, 0.04301826, 0.044554748, 0.015037486, 0.019013913, -0.058508504, 0.034006786, -0.027283128, 0.009905593, 0.031068306, 0.04427231, -0.1345456, -0.036378432, -0.0042537744, 0.0017605212, -0.03283253, -0.019044291, -0.03430978, -0.015089578, 0.026248224, -0.03894418, 0.03373245, 0.052202024, 0.029751234, 0.02296319, -0.019030957, 0.01854121, -0.06058132, 0.03401693, -0.0339015, -0.040226348, 0.012949265, -0.029456371, 0.07442418, -0.0075378143, 0.042045552, 0.03885537, -0.002119692, -0.031659212, 0.010186763, 0.